{
  "texts": [
    "For instance-dependent noise, we use the part-dependent noise from PDN [43] with noise rate η ∈ {0.2, 0.4}, where the noise is synthesized based on the DNN prediction error.",
    "For realworld noise, we use the \"Worst\" label set of CIFAR-10N and the \"Noisy\" label set of CIFAR-100N [52], respectively.",
    "The noise in CIFAR-10N and CIFAR-100N is generated based on human annotation errors.Noise generation for image segmentation.",
    "To evaluate the model's robustness against low-quality annotations, we follow the methodology from [53].",
    "In this approach, a portion of the training data is randomly sampled with probability η α ∈ {0.3, 0.5, 0.7}, and morphological transformations are applied, with noise levels controlled by η β ∈ {0.5, 0.7}."
  ]
}